# Forms layout (PEP Web)

Layout page: `/preview/full-page-popup` (sidebar **Layout → full page popup**).
Canonical Figma: [新增活動 `477:19891`](https://www.figma.com/design/IZ6algHkFp6Z2a5dYiS1hC/PEP?node-id=477-19891).
Table body Figma: [Timeslots `813:35945`](https://www.figma.com/design/IZ6algHkFp6Z2a5dYiS1hC/PEP?node-id=813-35945).

## Recipe (mandatory)

| Slot | Block / component | Notes |
|------|-------------------|--------|
| Dialog shell | `Dialog` + `fullPagePopupDialogContentClassName` | Edge-to-edge (`inset-0`), no margin |
| Header | `PepPopupHeader` | Figma `header/Popup` — not `PepPageHeader` |
| Left nav | `FormMenu` + `FormMenuItem` | Block → Form Menu |
| Body | `LibraryField` in `FormsFieldStack` | Field gap-2 inside; stack gap-6 between fields |
| Body (table) | Pending Table Cell rows | Register new cells in `table-cell-registry.ts` before use |
| Footer | `FormBottom` | Figma `Form_bottom` — progress + Cancel / Save |
| Body surface | `surface="card"` (form) / `"plain"` (table) | Table body: no outline / elevation |

Compose with `FormsLayout` from `@/components/forms-layout`.

## Pending workflow (mandatory)

When a layout introduces **new table cell compositions**, add `tier: 'pending'` rows to `table-cell-registry.ts` and previews in `TableCellBlockPage.tsx` **before** using them in the layout. Same pattern as Field §3 and Block → Table Cell Pending.

## Files

| File | Role |
|------|------|
| `components/forms-layout.tsx` | `FormsLayout`, `FormsFieldStack`, `fullPagePopupDialogContentClassName` |
| `components/pep-chrome.tsx` | `PepPopupHeader` |
| `components/form-bottom.tsx` | `FormBottom` |
| `components/form-menu.tsx` | Form Menu |
| `pages/FormsLayoutPage.tsx` | `FullPagePopupPage` — Layout docs + demos |
| `pages/FormBottomBlockPage.tsx` | Block → Form bottom |
| `pages/PopupHeaderBlockPage.tsx` | Block → Header-Popup |

## Anti-patterns

- Using `PepPageHeader` inside a form dialog.
- Rebuilding progress + Cancel/Save markup instead of `FormBottom`.
- Page-local field gaps instead of `LibraryField` + `FormsFieldStack`.
- Dialog inset margin (`inset-3`) on full-page popups — use `fullPagePopupDialogContentClassName`.
